{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NZ9pbQ9t27yR61EbNyZ6Ep","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The case setup requires:\n1. `es-alpha` cluster (3 nodes) with configmap `es-alpha-config` - this is the \"prod\" cluster with log data\n2. `es-beta` cluster (1 node) with configmap `es-beta-config` - this is the \"dev\" cluster\n\nThe \"drift\" bug is that `search-http` points to `es-beta` when it should point to `es-alpha`.\n\nThe current state only has `es-cluster` (3 nodes) which is the bootstrap environment from a prior stage. I need to:\n1. Apply the configmaps for both clusters\n2. Deploy the StatefulSets for `es-alpha` and `es-beta`\n3. Create the services with `search-http` correctly pointing to `es-alpha`\n4. Wait for both clusters to become healthy\n5. Seed data into `es-alpha` using the log-writer via `search-direct`\n6. Deploy the `log-reader`\n\nI should probably delete the existing `es-cluster` first since it's using 3 nodes and would conflict with the new setup - running 7 ES pods total (3 for es-alpha, 1 for es-beta, plus the existing 3) might exceed the kind cluster's capacity.\n\nActually, I'm wondering if the existing `es-cluster` is already meant to be `es-alpha` with data already in it. If so, I could just add `es-beta` and point `search-http` to the existing cluster. But the label mismatch is a problem - `es-cluster` uses `app: es-cluster`, not `app: es-alpha`, so the service selector wouldn't work correctly. I think the cleaner approach is to delete `es-cluster` and start fresh with the proper `es-alpha` and `es-beta` setup.\n\nLet me check the test.yaml to understand what the precondition was supposed to initialize.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1873,"cache_read_input_tokens":40612,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephem